BLACKROC is proud to be partnering with a global brand and household name,
that is nationally recognised for empowering every day Australians. They are
looking for a Senior DevOps Engineer who will be focused on the redevelopment
of their infrastructure with a heavy emphasis on automation to improve
customer experience and business agility.  
  
This role would suit someone with a background in Software Engineering who has
moved into a Cloud or DevOps career.  
  
** Responsibilities: **   

  * Contribute to the design and implementation of business applications deployed as Infrastructure as Code 
  * Work on building standardised CI/CD pipelines 
  * Ensure solutions are performant, secure, scalable and reliable 
  * Ensure monitors, alerts and recovery processes are in place from day one and defined as code 
  * Document and share knowledge across teams 
** Experience: **   

  * Multiple years experience with AWS 
  * Solid background in the provisioning of Infrastructure and Configuration as Code utilising Kubernetes and AWS 
  * Working knowledge of Git source control and best practices 
  * Extensive experience with software development teams and IT operations 
  * Two or more years experience automating production solutions with Terraform 
For more information on this opportunity please contact Matthew Walsh at
BLACKROC. Alternatively, if this isn’t the right opportunity for you but
you’re interested in other opportunities within the Data, Cloud &
Infrastructure industry in Brisbane, feel free to contact me.  

